# News App Backend Service
This is a backend service for a news app where I have created authentication APIs and news creation APIs, and I have also used features like API hit limit, logging files,send emails, Redis, and queue.

# Technolgy
NodeJS
ExpressJS 
PostgresSQL for database 
PrismaORM  
POSTMAN for Testing


# Steps:
1. npm init -y
2. write this "type":"module" in package.json file for es6 javascript
3. change script ""test" to "start":"node serve.js", "server":"nodemon server.js"" in package.json file
4. npm i express dotenv nodemon
5. create .env file
6. for validation npm i @vinejs/vine
7. npm i prisma --save-dev
8. npx prisma
9. npx prisma init
10. npm i @prisma/client
11. npx prisma migrate dev --name any_name
12. npm run server
13. setup postgresSQL db
14. npm i bcryptjs jsonwebtoken uuid express-fileupload
15. npm i helmet cors for secure http headers
16. npm i express-rate-limit for api hits
17. npm i express-redis-cache for caching (note; first install docker)
18. npm i winston for logging files
19. npm i nodemailer for send emails
20. npm i bullmq for queue
